Nieuwerkerk aan den IJssel is a railway station in Nieuwerkerk aan den IJssel, Netherlands. The station is located on the Utrechtâ€“Rotterdam railway between Gouda and Rotterdam Centraal. It was opened on 21 May 1971 and is mostly used by commuters. The train services are operated by Nederlandse Spoorwegen.


== Train services ==
The following services call at Nieuwerkerk a/d IJssel:

2x per hour local service (sprinter) Uitgeest - Amsterdam - Woerden - Gouda - Rotterdam
2x per hour local service (sprinter) Rotterdam - Gouda Goverwelle


